## Angular Component Best Practices

### Component Structure

```typescript
import {
  Component,
  signal,
  computed,
  inject,
  input,
  output,
} from "@angular/core";
import { ChangeDetectionStrategy } from "@angular/core";

@Component({
  selector: "app-example",
  templateUrl: "./example.html",
  styleUrls: ["./example.scss"],
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  imports: [
    /* standalone imports */
  ],
})
export class Example {
  // Use inject() instead of constructor injection
  private router = inject(Router);
  private authService = inject(Auth);

  // Use input() and output() functions instead of decorators
  title = input<string>("Default Title");
  users = input<User[]>([]);
  formSubmitted = output<FormData>();

  // Use signals for local state
  isLoading = signal(false);
  isActive = signal(false);

  // Use computed() for derived state
  isFormValid = computed(() => !this.nameError() && !this.emailError());
  backgroundColor = computed(() => (this.isActive() ? "#e3f2fd" : "#ffffff"));
}
```

### Key Component Rules

1. âœ… All components use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
2. âœ… Use `inject()` function instead of constructor injection
3. âœ… Use `input()` and `output()` functions instead of `@Input()` and `@Output()` decorators
4. âœ… Use signals for all local state
5. âœ… Use `computed()` for all derived state
6. âœ… Keep components small and focused (single responsibility)
7. âœ… All components are standalone (no NgModules)

## Template Best Practices

### Use Native Control Flow (NOT *ngIf, *ngFor, \*ngSwitch)

```html
<!-- âœ… Good: Use native control flow -->
@if (isVisible()) {
<h2>{{ title() }}</h2>
} @for (user of users(); track user.id) {
<div class="user-item">
  <span>{{ user.name }}</span>
</div>
} @switch (status()) { @case ('loading') {
<div class="loading">Loading...</div>
} @case ('success') {
<div class="success">Success!</div>
} @default {
<div class="default">Default state</div>
} }

<!-- âŒ Bad: Don't use old syntax -->
<div *ngIf="isVisible()">...</div>
<div *ngFor="let user of users()">...</div>
```

### Use Class and Style Bindings (NOT ngClass/ngStyle)

```html
<!-- âœ… Good: Use direct bindings -->
<div [class.active]="isActive()" [class.disabled]="isDisabled()">
  Dynamic classes
</div>

<div [style.background-color]="backgroundColor()" [style.color]="textColor()">
  Dynamic styles
</div>

<!-- âŒ Bad: Don't use ngClass/ngStyle -->
<div [ngClass]="{'active': isActive()}">...</div>
<div [ngStyle]="{'background-color': backgroundColor()}">...</div>
```

### Always Use Async Pipe for Observables

```html
<!-- âœ… Good -->
@if (user$ | async; as user) {
<div>{{ user.name }}</div>
}

<!-- âŒ Bad: Don't manually subscribe in templates -->
```

## Service Best Practices

### Service Structure

```typescript
import { Injectable, inject, signal } from "@angular/core";

@Injectable({
  providedIn: "root", // Always use root provider
})
export class Auth {
  // Use inject() instead of constructor injection
  private router = inject(Router);
  private notification = inject(NotificationService);

  // Use signals for service state
  currentUser = signal<User | null>(null);
  isAuthenticated = computed(() => this.currentUser() !== null);

  // Service methods...
}
```

### Key Service Rules

1. âœ… All services use `providedIn: 'root'`
2. âœ… Use `inject()` function instead of constructor injection
3. âœ… Single responsibility principle
4. âœ… Use signals for state management

## State Management

### Use Signals for State

```typescript
// âœ… Local component state
isSubmitting = signal(false);
errorMessage = signal("");

// âœ… Computed state
isFormValid = computed(
  () => this.email().length > 0 && this.password().length > 0
);

// âœ… Effects for side effects
effect(() => {
  if (this.isAuthenticated()) {
    this.router.navigate(["/dashboard"]);
  }
});
```

### State Rules

1. âœ… Use signals for all local state
2. âœ… Use computed() for all derived state
3. âœ… Use effect() for side effects
4. âœ… Keep state transformations pure and predictable
5. âœ… Use RxJS only for complex asynchronous operations

